Rating: 2
While I prefer the classic Caesar and not this mayonnaisey creamy rendition, I was intrigued by the rave reviews and just made a 1/3 batch for my 19-year old son for lunch. He's an anchovy and Caesar-salad lover, and gave me the thumbs up on this. I did have to thin the dressing a bit with olive oil. For those like me who prefer the more traditional, try this: sprinkle your wooden salad bowl with coarse salt, then rub with a cut clove of garlic. Then crush the garlic in the bowl, add a dash of Tabasco, a dash of Worcester, about 1/2 tsp dry mustard, a healthy grind of pepper, 3 tbsp EV olive oil, more or less, juice of 1/2 very juicy lemon, and one egg yolk. Whisk in the bowl to emulsify. Add your romaine and toss. Grate your parmesan or pecorino romano over the greens, to your heart's delight. Then add your favorite croutons and anchovies and toss again.

