Rating: 2
Wanted to share the BEST caesar dressing I've come across: 1/2 TB dijon, 2 garlic cloves peeled, 3 anchovies, 1 TB Worcestershire, 1 TSP hot sauce, 3/4 tsp black pepper (fresh ground is better), 1/4 cup fresh lemon juice, 1/4 cup fresh grated parmesan, 1/4 cup extra virgin olive oil. Blend all in blender,except oil, then add slowly the oil. Taste, and see if you need any salt (depending on how salty your parmesan is.) I just add a pinch. I got this from Gourmet magazine and have made it so many times, sometimes adding grilled chicken or shrimp.It keeps for one week in the fridge. The key is using fresh ingredients, especially the lemon juice and parmesan. This is better than the finest restaurant!! The hot sauce gives it a "kick",without making it spicy. You wouldn't even know it was there, but it adds that special dimension to the dressing. That's what I found makes all the difference!Oh, and for the croutons...why bother to make them? I use Chatham Village large cut Caesar croutons. Getit in the produce section of my supermarket. Also great are the garlic and butter ones!! (kids eat them out of the bag! Hope everyone loves it!

