My husband is fussy about Caesar salads, but there were no complaints when I served this version. Crouton tip: Slice the garlic in half and soak in the olive oil as long as possible, then pour it all into a pan to saute. If you can plan ahead, soak it overnight. The oil will absorb enough garlic flavor so that it will not be necessary to saute it, avoiding any possibility of "scorched" garlic flavor.

