Rating: 4
MMMMMM. This is all I heard when I decided to serve this salad at a small dinner party. It's that good. I made a few changes, based on some of the other reviews: no mayo at all (replaced it with 1/3 cup of olive oil, and one large egg yolk) and I cut the garlic down to two (large) cloves. I reduced the amount of anchovies to three fillets (couldn't find anchovies with capers, so I just used plain). I also used only a half teaspoon of the dijon mustard because I don't like my Caesars tangy, and added a tiny bit of black pepper to the dressing. The croutons were the first I've made that have really turned out well. I seasoned them with a light sprinkling of garlic salt in place of the table salt. Topped with some freshly grated Parmesan Reggiano, this salad is heaven in a bowl. The best I've tried.

