The best caesar salad dressing I've made! My husband & I are known to our friends as the king & queen of garlic and I always double the garlic called for in most recipes. Based on the comments I read, I stuck to the 3 cloves called for. It was just right. I also used 3 anchovie filets (not with capers) and added a dash of tabasco for kick! I also adjusted the mayo (low fat) to 1/2 cup and added 1/4 cup of olive oil at the end while blending the dressing. I had shavings of good parmesan cheese instead of the regular grated version and put 3 grilled garlic shrimp on top of each plate. My guests and I were in heaven. This recipe is definately a keeper.

